('Cambridge', 'Snow', 'Male', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Snow brings a warm, attachment-focused approach to complex psychological conditions. He works across the lifespan and is especially skilled in supporting families, navigating personality and mood challenges.', 1200, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE),
('Serenity', 'Wells', 'Female', 'Counselling Psychologist', 'Dr. Wells is fluent in English, Zulu, and Xhosa and brings deep cultural sensitivity to her practice. She specialises in helping clients navigate grief, depression, and relationship difficulties.', 1100, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE),
('Lucas', 'TChalla', 'Male', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. TChalla uses a trauma-focused, evidence-based approach to support clients dealing with trauma, mood disorders, and personality challenges. He offers individual, family, and group therapy.', 1300, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, TRUE),
('Nakia', 'Parker', 'Female', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Parker works with a wide range of presenting concerns across all age groups. Her relational, narrative approach helps clients make meaning of their experiences and build resilience.', 1150, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE),
('Wanda', 'Mokoena', 'Female', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Mokoena specialises in supporting adults through anxiety, low mood, and major life changes. Her mindfulness-informed approach helps clients develop lasting coping strategies.', 1200, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE),
('Madison', 'Govender', 'Female', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Govender is a trauma specialist with deep expertise in PTSD and complex trauma. She is fluent in English and Tamil and known for her culturally sensitive, compassionate approach.', 1350, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE),
('Natasha', 'Dlamini', 'Female', 'Industrial Psychologist', 'Dr. Dlamini is the workplace and career specialist at Serenity. She helps clients navigate burnout, financial stress, and career transitions. She speaks Zulu, Swati, and English.', 1400, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE),
('Peter', 'Mercer', 'Male', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Mercer takes a focused, evidence-based approach to anxiety, sleep difficulties, and mood disorders. His work is grounded in CBT and DBT with particular expertise in sleep-related conditions.', 1100, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE),
('Tony', 'Livingston', 'Male', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Livingston supports adults navigating significant life changes, loss, and the development of resilient coping skills. His positive, person-centred approach creates a safe space for growth.', 1050, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE),
('Bruce', 'Maryland', 'Male', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Maryland offers online therapy for adults dealing with anxiety, depression, and workplace stress. His strength-based, coaching-oriented approach gives him a grounded perspective on how the mind and environment interact.', 1000, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE),
('Matthew', 'Stark', 'Male', 'Counselling Psychologist', 'Dr. Stark supports adults navigating career transitions and workplace stress. He draws on existential and motivational approaches, alongside positive psychology and mindfulness-based techniques, to help clients rebuild motivation and find clarity in their professional lives.', 1100, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, TRUE),
('Fury', 'Khang', 'Male', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Khang specialises in relationship and family dynamics. He helps couples and individuals navigate conflict, improve communication, and rebuild connection.', 1200, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE),
('Ramonda', 'Obiagu', 'Female', 'Clinical Psychologist', 'Dr. Obiagu draws on psychoanalytic and Jungian traditions to help clients explore the deeper roots of depression, anxiety, and emotional disturbance.', 1250, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE);